40|$|Abstract: This paper {{contributes}} to the literature on economic growth by seeking to join several lines of research on structural factors in a more fully specified framework, on the one hand, and by making this more inclusive supply side to interact with demand factors in a model of export-led growth. Balance-of-payments constraints influence the adoption of investment-specific technological change which requires the <b>import</b> <b>of</b> <b>capital</b> goods, while the sectoral allocation of physical and human capital is likewise revealead to be crucial for growth, both results having important policy implications...|$|E
